{"search_data": "West BengalSelf Help Group (SHG) Scheme in West Bengal \u2013 700 Crore for 50 Lakh Rural WomenWest Bengal Self Help Group (SHG) Scheme \u2013 3 PhasesWB govt. will implement this scheme in 3 phases which are as follows:-Identification & Training (1st Phase) \u2013 In first phase, the state govt. will identify rural women who are not covered under SHG network. After identification process, govt. will provide Skill Development training and its entire cost will be borne by the state co-operation department.Loans to Rural Women (2nd Phase) \u2013 West Bengal govt. is going to provide loans to women in villages. Accordingly, govt. will give interest subsidy on loans from different cooperative banks and cooperative societies. Henceforth, women this get these loans for self employment at low interest rates.Promotion & Marketing of SHG Products (3rd Phase) \u2013 The final phase of this scheme will include promotion and marketing of the products of these SHGs. For this reason, govt. will open SHG outlets and will also create a network of other state govt. departments such as agriculture marketing, food & supplies and small & medium industries department."}